					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-lonewolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1300064); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1300064&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205305" alt="Dr Lonewolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1300064)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-lonewolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1300064); return false;" >Dr Lonewolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1418917749 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Dec 2014 15:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2183644">
									

<p>I just finished reading Sandpaper and After School. Creepy, confusing, yet giving me enough breadcrumbs to just HAVE to wait for the next bit of excitement&#8230;GREAT story.</p>
<p>Just because there is not a specific SCP does not exclude it from being on here. There are a number of &quot;anomalous&quot; actions in this story, and multiple things that would be qualified as SCPs. The town, the old school, the hamster, Jonathan, the &quot;ventilation&quot; system; all building an incredible level of creepy. If the story concluded with the nice policemen giving everyone pills&#8230;&quot;wait, why are the police here?&quot; &#8230;you could bridge the foundation itself in. Seriously want more.</p>

							</div>

								
					
