				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/trennerdios" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1277937); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1277937&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205305" alt="trennerdios" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1277937)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/trennerdios" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1277937); return false;" >trennerdios</a></span> <span class="odate time_1442429505 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Sep 2015 18:51</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2376681">
									

<p>It's funny, I remember when I was excited by the prospect of 1048 showing up in CB at some point. Then, when I found out it had actually been added to the game, I suddenly realized why my SCP's rating had suddenly spiked a bit, and I became a bit disappointed and jaded. I remember being irritated when 106 and 96, which 1048 had previously surpassed, had suddenly risen back up past it on the top rated pages due to CB's increase in popularity after being featured on popular youtubers' channels, and now my own SCP was doing the same thing. That was a year ago though, and things have leveled out a bit, and I think it's pretty cool that 1048 is in the game. I didn't know they had added 1048-A though, I'll have to look that up.</p>

							</div>

								
					
